{{Cleanup FJC Bio}}
'''David Jackson Davis''' (October 15, 1878 &ndash; December 7, 1938) was a [[United States federal judge]].

Davis was born in [[Weedowee, Alabama]]. He received a [[LL.B]] from [[Yale University]] in 1906. He was in private practice of law in [[Birmingham, Alabama]] from 1906 to 1935. 

Davis was a federal judge to the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of Alabama]]. Davis received a [[recess appointment]] from Franklin D. Roosevelt on December 10, 1935, to a seat vacated by [[Grubb William I.]]. nominated on January 6, 1936; He was confirmed by the [[United States Senate]] on January 22, 1936, and received commission on January 28, 1936. Davis<!-- -->'s service was terminated on December 7, 1938, due to death.

